content:
Create a Channel Menu Deployment

The setup node for Embedded Channel Menu is available only in Lightning Experience.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata
To create and edit Salesforce Sites:	Customize Application
To edit public access settings for Salesforce Sites:	Manage Users

Choose a deployment channel in your org:

From Service Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Channel Menu, and click Channel Menu.
Select and View an existing deployment or create one.

If you add a new deployment:

Give it a name that is easy to remember (spaces are OK).
Add your API name without spaces.
Set the site endpoint.
Enable Guest Access to the Support API for the site you use for the Channel Menu:
Go to Salesforce Admin Setup > Sites or search for Sites in the Quick Find box.
Click on your selected Site Label and Edit in the Site Detail section.
Check the Guest Access to the Support API check box.
Add the Quick Actions associated with your Embedded Service deployment from the Available Quick Actions box to the Selected Quick Actions box and Save.
